header.gameNote: C-USA MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - 1st ROUND AT TULSA OK

article.headline: UAB 53, SMU 52
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Jordan Swing scored 17 points, including a layup with 9 seconds to play, and UAB beat SMU 53-52 in the opener of the Conference USA tournament on Wednesday. Swing had a team-high nine rebounds and was 7 of 13 from the field for the game. Rod Rucker had 11 points. UAB was up 32-23 at halftime and led until Brian Bernardi hit two free throws to put the Mustangs up 52-51 with 29 seconds remaining. Swing's layup put the Blazers (16-16) back on top. No. 10 seed SMU missed a jumper with a second to play. Jalen Jones led SMU (15-17) with 13 points and 10 rebounds. Cannen Cunningham had 11 points. No. 7 seed UAB will play No. 2 seed Southern Mississippi on Thursday in the quarterfinals. Head coach Larry Brown, who is the only coach to win an NCAA and NBA title, ends his first season at SMU.
